public boolean process(Exchange exchange, AsyncCallback originalCallback) {
    // 1. Create after-task for cleanup callbacks
    Object[] states = new Object[statefulAdvices];
    CamelInternalTask afterTask = new AsyncAfterTask(states);

    // 2. Execute ALL advices BEFORE in order (lines 329-339)
    for (int i = 0; i < advices.size(); i++) {
        CamelInternalProcessorAdvice<?> task = advices.get(i);
        Object state = task.before(exchange);
        if (task.hasState()) {
            states[j++] = state;
        }
    }

    // 3. Check for debugger skip
    if (exchange.getProperty(ExchangePropertyKey.SKIP_OVER) == Boolean.TRUE) {
        originalCallback.done(true);
        return true;
    }

    // 4. Delegate to wrapped processor
    if (exchange.isTransacted()) {
        return processTransacted(exchange, afterTask);  // Sync
    }
    return processNonTransacted(exchange, afterTask);   // Async
}
```

**Transacted vs Non-Transacted (Lines 376-440):**

**Non-Transacted (Lines 376-400):**
