## Complete Process Flow Diagram

```
Exchange.process() via Channel
    ↓
Channel (wrapping interceptors) → ErrorHandler → Interceptor-N → ... → Interceptor-1
    ↓
DefaultChannel.getOutput() → returns wrapped chain
    ↓
CamelInternalProcessor.process()
    ├─ FOR EACH advice: execute BEFORE callbacks
    ├─ IF transacted: call processor.process(exchange) synchronously
    └─ IF non-transacted: call processor.process(exchange, asyncCallback)
        ├─ Processor = Pipeline
        │   ├─ Creates PipelineTask
        │   ├─ Schedules task on ReactiveExecutor
        │   └─ Returns false (async)
        │
        └─ PipelineTask.run() (executed by ReactiveExecutor)
            ├─ Check stop conditions
            ├─ Get processor at current index
            ├─ Call processor.process(exchange, this) - passes itself as callback
            ├─ ON CALLBACK (sync or async):
            │   ├─ If more processors: increment index, reschedule self
            │   └─ If done: invoke original callback
            └─ Original callback → AsyncAfterTask.done()
                ├─ Execute all AFTER advices in reverse order
                ├─ Invoke original callback
                └─ Release pooled task
```

