Processor errorHandler = ((ModelCamelContext) camelContext).getModelReifierFactory()
    .createErrorHandler(route, builder, null);
prepareErrorHandlerAware(route, errorHandler);
```

**prepareErrorHandlerAware()** (Lines 422-429):
```java
private void prepareErrorHandlerAware(Route route, Processor errorHandler) {
    List<Processor> processors = route.filter("*");  // Get all processors
    for (Processor p : processors) {
        if (p instanceof ErrorHandlerAware errorHandlerAware) {
            errorHandlerAware.setErrorHandler(errorHandler);
        }
    }
}
```

This ensures all processors in the route are aware of the error handler for fine-grained control.

### Interceptor Wiring Flow

**Three Levels of Interceptors (ProcessorReifier line 662-665):**
```java
List<InterceptStrategy> interceptors = new ArrayList<>();
interceptors.addAll(camelContext.getCamelContextExtension().getInterceptStrategies());  // Global
interceptors.addAll(route.getInterceptStrategies());                                     // Route-scoped
interceptors.addAll(definition.getInterceptStrategies());                                // Node-scoped
```

**Wrapping Order (DefaultChannel lines 232-234):**
- Interceptors are sorted by `@Ordered` annotation
- Reversed so first interceptor wraps last (becomes innermost, closest to processor)
- Each wraps the previous result: `strategy.wrapProcessorInInterceptors(...)`

**Result Chain Structure:**
```
Output 
  ↓ (wrapped by Interceptor1)
Interceptor1
  ↓ (wrapped by Interceptor2)
Interceptor2
  ↓ (wrapped by Interceptor3)
Interceptor3
  ↓
NextProcessor
```

