## Summary: Complete Flow

```
1. RouteDefinition (XML/Java DSL) → Model representation

2. RouteReifier.createRoute() called
   ├─ Create Route object (DefaultRoute)
   ├─ Resolve input endpoint
   ├─ Configure route properties
   ├─ For each output definition:
   │  └─ Get reifier (ProcessorReifier subclass)
   │     └─ Create Processor
   │     └─ Wrap in Channel
   │        ├─ Apply interceptors (3 levels)
   │        ├─ Apply error handler
   │        └─ Wire debugger/tracer/management
   │     └─ Add to eventDrivenProcessors
   ├─ Create RoutePipeline from eventDrivenProcessors
   ├─ Wrap in InternalProcessor with UnitOfWork advice
   ├─ Add cross-cutting concerns (policies, contracts, etc.)
   ├─ Inject error handler into ErrorHandlerAware processors
   └─ Return Route

3. Route.start() when CamelContext starts
   ├─ Create Consumer from input endpoint
   ├─ Consumer receives messages
   └─ Passes to Route.processor (RoutePipeline)

4. Message flows through processor chain
   ├─ RoutePipeline routes to first Processor
   ├─ Each Channel:
   │  ├─ Applies interceptors
   │  ├─ Applies error handling
   │  └─ Routes to nextProcessor
   └─ Final processor sends to output endpoint(s)

5. RouteController manages lifecycle
   ├─ Start/stop routes
   ├─ Monitor health
   └─ Integrate with supervision
```

